commit.message: Add ENVIRONMENT to man-page.
doc: Firefox from version 60 moved audio to the main process

change cmake variable type to BOOL

Turned out is was BOOL, not BOOLEAN all along. Just recently CMake started
to warn about it.

stream: check ALSA API results as <0 rather than !=0

Most ALSA API functions that return status, declare return value as
either 0 or negative error code. However some functions like
snd_pcm_hw_params_any() return just int. In most cases it's the same 0 or
negative, but as was found in #108, it may return positive values too.

ALSA lib internally uses "< 0" for return value checking.
Merge pull request #101 from dscharrer
link libpulse-mainloop-glib with libpulse too

link libpulse-simple against libpulse

Without this dlopen("libpulse-simple.so.0") will fail if the process
hasn't already loaded libpulse.so.0.

This makes apulse work for Unreal Engine 4 games.

commit.message:
Use alsa API properly

Consumers are expected to use <alsa/asoundlib.h> instead of
<asoundlib.h>.

This is in preparation of an change to pkgconfig(alsa) to
not pollute CFLAGS with -I/usr/include/alsa anymore

Signed-off-by: Olaf Hering <olaf@aepfle.de>

commit.message:
added default case
to avoid compiler warnings of unhandled (library-private) enum values

This avoids the compiler warning "enumeration value ‘SND_PCM_STATE_PRIVATE1’ not handled
in switch [-Wswitch]"

This library-private PCM state is used internally only (see
https://www.alsa-project.org/alsa-doc/alsa-lib/group___p_c_m.html#ga61ac499cb3701ce536d4d83725908860).

Merge branch 'XRevan86-master'

Fix compatibility with PulseAudio 11.99+ headers.

lower pa_cvolume_scale_mask constification version to 11.99

There is a pre-release version 11.99, which already have parameter type
changed.
fix compatibility with PulseAudio 12.x+

Revert "use time_new rather than defer_new for delayed callbacks"

This reverts commit b3f2a8e05674401e83760eb7c96607d33d08380b.

Revert "mainloop: stop waking mainloop on defer_new"

This reverts commit 7d5f47f361f1c1ec3475127adac8a27f0096d9d7.

mainloop: stop waking mainloop on defer_new

It's not necessary. Any time is fine for deferred events.

use time_new rather than defer_new for delayed callbacks

Callbacks passed to defer_new() are not supposed to start immediately.
Instead, they could be started anytime later, during next mainloop
iteration. So, they are not reliable.
